summary:
Killing Eve...
It really didn't pull off what Hannibal did - an investigator genuinely being seduced, falling for a killer
Which...
body:
Killing Eve…

It really didn’t pull off what Hannibal did - an investigator genuinely being seduced, falling for a killer

Which leaves it hanging wide open looking like a nasty predatory lesbian trope

And villanelle was kind of an obnoxious zany (manic pixie?) pyschopath

But hey I got to watch a really cool Asian American woman solve crimes and a young woman murder the shit very competently out of a lot of people

And the soundtrack was killer too
